shire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Goosnargh, Preston district, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Goosnargh, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Sutherland, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Sutherland, Scotland, United Kingdom","Kildonan, Kilmory, North Ayrshire, Ayrshire and Arran, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Kilmory, North Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Mure","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Italian (Sicily): variant of   Morea  .","Scottish: variant of   Muir  .","English: occupational name from Old French <i>muer</i> ‘mewer’, i.e. someone who tended to hawks in the cages in which they were kept while moulting. Compare   Mew  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Mura","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Japanese Akio, Hideo, Masao, Nanako, Tsutomu, Yoshi.  French Alphonse, Amie, Henri.","German: altered form of some similar (like-sounding) German or perhaps French surname. It is also common in France (Alsace), where it was first recorded in the form <i>Morrau</i>, later <i>Murra(w)</i>.","Italian (southern Sardinia): topographic name or nickname from Sardinian <i>mura</i> ‘mulberry’ or ‘blackberry’."]},{"name":"Muir","meanings":["Scottish: topographic name for someone who lived on a moor, from Older Scots <i>muir</i> ‘moor’ (an expanse of bare, wild upland country). There has been some confusion with   Mure  ."]},{"name":"Morea","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Saverio, Domenic, Ferdinando, Rocco.  Spanish Manuel, Carlos, Cesar, Elvira, Jesus, Mauricio.","Italian (Apulia): from the personal name <i>Morea</i>, originally a habitational name from Morea, the medieval name of the Greek region of Peloponnese, named as the land of mulberry trees, from <i>mōrea</i> ‘mulberry’.","Spanish and Catalan: habitational name from any of the places called Morea, in Badajoz, Navarre, and Lleida provinces."]}]},{"name":"Alison","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a very common medieval name, a Norman French diminutive of   Alice .  Despite its early popularity, it became quite rare in England in the 16th century. However, it survived in Scotland, with the result that until its revival in England in the 20th century it had a strongly Scottish flavour."],"variants":[{"name":"Alyson","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alison ."]},{"name":"Allyson","meanings":["Respelling of   Alison ."]},{"name":"Allison","meanings":["Respelling of   Alison .  This is the more common form of the name in the United States."]},{"name":"Alysoun","meanings":["Medieval spelling of   Alison  , which has enjoyed some currency since the 20th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alison Mure was born on 25 February 1477, in Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. She married John Eccles in 1490, in Kilmory, North Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1536, in Kilmory, North Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 59."},"et":{"25 February 1477–1536":"25. veebruar 1477–1536","1460–1550":"1460–1550","1490–1560":"1490–1560","1514–1580":"1514–1580","1525–1588":"1525–1588","1477–1536":"1477–1536","1514":"1514","1525":"1525","1536":"1536","1588":"1588","1477":"1477","25 February 1477":"25. veebruar 1477","1550":"1550","1560":"1560","1460":"1460","1580":"1580","1490":"1490","liv. 25 Feb 1477":"25. veebruar 1477","Caldwell, Glasgow, Lanark, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Goosnargh, Preston district, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Goosnargh, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sutherland, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Sutherland, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Kildonan, Kilmory, North Ayrshire, Ayrshire and Arran, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Kilmory, North Ayrshir